t%20Donald%20Trump's%20administration%20violated%20legal%20requirements%20governing%20the%20layoff%20of%20federal%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20names%20multiple%20federal%20agencies%20and%20their%20secretaries%20as%20defendants%2C%20claims%20that%20federal%20agencies%20failed%20to%20provide%20the%20legally%20required%20notice%20before%20carrying%20out%20the%20terminations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20specifically%20accused%20the%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management%20(OPM)%20of%20unlawfully%20directing%20federal%20agencies%20to%20conduct%20mass%20terminations%20of%20probationary%20employees%20%26quot%3Bsuddenly%20and%20without%20any%20advance%20notice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProbationary%20employees%20are%20typically%20workers%20who%20have%20served%20in%20the%20role%20for%20less%20than%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20federal%20law%2C%20agencies%20must%20generally%20give%20employees%2060%20days'%20written%20notice%20of%20a%20%26quot%3BReduction-in-Force%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20are%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20when%2050%20or%20more%20employees%20within%20an%20agency%20receive%20these%20notices%2C%20federal%20laws%20require%20the%20agency%20to%20notify%20state%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20said%20that%20these%20notices%20serve%20critical%20purposes%3A%20they%20give%20employees%20time%20to%20find%20new%20jobs%20and%20budget%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20income%2C%20and%20they%20allow%20states%20to%20better%20mobilize%20resources%2C%20including%20job%20placement%20services%2C%20training%20opportunities%2C%20and%20connections%20to%20social%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20month%2C%20the%20new%20Administration%20has%20run%20roughshod%20over%20the%20RIF%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20it%20said%20that%20employees%20and%20their%20families%20are%20%26quot%3Bstruggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20plaintiff%20states%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20%26quot%3Bscramble%20and%20expend%20additional%20resources%20to%20identify%20even%20which%20agencies%20have%20conducted%20layoffs%20and%20which%20affected%20employees%20require%20support.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorneys%20general%20involved%20represent%20the%20states%20of%20Maryland%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20Arizona%2C%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20Delaware%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Nevada%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20New%20York%2C%20Oregon%2C%20Rhode%20Island%2C%20Vermont%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Trump%20administration's%20illegal%20mass%20firings%20of%20federal%20workers%20are%20a%20slap%20in%20the%20face%20to%20those%20who%20have%20spent%20their%20careers%20serving%20our%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20New%20York%20AG%20Letitia%20James%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorneys%20general%20are%20seeking%20a%20court%20order%20to%20stop%20further%20mass%20layoffs%20without%20the%20required%20notice%20period%2C%20and%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20workers%20laid%20off%20since%20January%2020%2C%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20probationary%20employees%20have%20been%20fired%20amid%20the%20push%20by%20the%20White%20House%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-job-cuts-layoffs-highest-level-2020-covid-pandemic-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20to%20shrink%20the%20federal%20workforce.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20San%20Francisco%20ruled%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-rules-trump-mass-firings-probationary-federal-employees-invalid-doge-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20OPM%20must%20withdraw%20memos%3C%2Fa%3E%20calling%20for%20other%20agencies%20to%20terminate%20probationary%20employees%2C%20saying%20the%20OPM%20had%20exceeded%20its%20legal%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20OPM%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-opm-memo-revise-probationary-employee-fire-doge-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equietly%20revised%20a%20memo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0about%20firing%3C%2Fspan%3E%20probationary%20employees%2C%20clarifying%20that%20individual%20agencies%2C%20not%20the%20OPM%2C%20are%20responsible%20for%20terminating%20federal%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F20-attorneys-general-sue-trump-administration-mass-federal-worker-firings-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741351200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cadc5869253ccddf989146%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F20-attorneys-general-sue-trump-administration-mass-federal-worker-firings-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Attorneys%20general%20are%20suing%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20saying%20federal%20agencies%20unlawfully%20fired%20probationary%20employees%20without%20the%20required%20notice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Nelken-Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F20-attorneys-general-sue-trump-administration-mass-federal-worker-firings-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aid%20operations%20in%20Gaza%20imperiled%20as%20millions%20of%20promised%20USAID%20dollars%20do%20not%20arrive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741351198000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsi