Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20not%20to%20like%20a%20person%20who's%20that%20smart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267d02a3b-3ce9-442d-b1d7-b4f393d24a3d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20could%20tell%20Bezos%20was%20on%20to%20something%20big%20when%20I%20started%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20joined%20the%20company%20in%20the%20late%2090s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ai-reasoning-model-nova-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20hiring%20like%20crazy.%20Bezos%20was%20on%20a%20mad%20mission%20to%20get%20big%20fast.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20got%20there%2C%20I%20started%20interviewing%20other%20candidates.%20At%20times%2C%20I%20was%20scheduled%20for%20two%20interviews%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20so%20I'd%20run%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20the%20rooms%20to%20ask%20them%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Amazon%20office%20was%20unlike%20the%20conventional%20startup%20atmosphere%20I%20was%20used%20to.%20The%20building%20was%20grungy%20and%20the%20offices%20were%20dark%20and%20dingy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20that%2C%20once%20you%20stepped%20into%20the%20building%2C%20there%20was%20a%20crackle%20in%20the%20air.%20You%20could%20feel%20that%20something%20really%20big%20was%20going%20on%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20was%20all%20centered%20on%20Jeff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fef6238c-78bf-4619-9d1e-47e0d3d7e84a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worked%20across%20multiple%20parts%20of%20the%20company%2C%20including%20on%20a%20secret%20project%20for%20Jeff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhired-at-amazon-after-learning-english-with-app-cambly-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20hired%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20asked%20my%20friend%20who%20left%20before%20me%20to%20deliver%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20After%20interviewing%2C%20I%20wound%20up%20in%20the%20technical%20program%20management%20organization.%20My%20job%20for%20the%20first%20year%20was%20to%20help%20coordinate%20projects%20that%20spanned%20across%20multiple%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20I%20spent%20roughly%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20in%20customer%20service%20tools%20and%20led%20the%20engineering%20team%20for%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20of%20that%20time.%20The%20craziest%20things%20would%20happen%20in%20that%20part%20of%20the%20company%3A%20There'd%20be%20transportation%20mishaps%2C%20and%20we'd%20send%20people%20the%20extraordinarily%20wrong%20thing%2C%20but%20then%20we'd%20go%20overboard%20trying%20to%20make%20things%20right%20for%20the%20customer.%20We%20had%20all%20the%20best%20stories.%20I%20then%20became%20an%20engineering%20manager%20in%20developer%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToward%20the%20end%20of%20my%20time%20at%20Amazon%2C%20Jeff%20asked%20me%20to%20work%20on%20a%20secret%20project.%20He%20was%20always%20dreaming%20up%20stuff%20and%20assigning%20tasks%20that%20seemed%20impossible.%20The%20project%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20something%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20enough%20about%20distributed%20computing%20to%20pull%20off%20what%20Jeff%20wanted%20in%20his%20desired%20timeframe.%20I%20felt%20the%20project%20wasn't%20feasible%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20I%20was%20scared%20to%20deliver%20that%20message%20to%20Jeff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20offered%20me%20a%20great%20package%2C%20so%20I%20left%20Amazon%20in%202005%20to%20work%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22553b053c-d6cb-4fdc-b990-f6f098bdc701%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20didn't%20like%20working%20at%20Amazon%2C%20but%20I%20actually%20really%20liked%20Jeff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20was%20a%20very%20hands-on%20leader.%20He'd%20often%20come%20to%20our%20customer%20service%20meetings%20and%20look%20at%20the%20data%20showing%20why%20customers%20were%20contacting%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20under%20other%20CEOs%2C%20including%20Google's%20Larry%20Page%20and%20Eric%20Schmidt%2C%20and%20they%20didn't%20typically%20pull%20senior%20employees%20together%20for%20impromptu%20chats%2C%20but%20Jeff%20would%20do%20this%20quite%20often.%20He'd%20reset%20us%20and%20change%20how%20everyone%20in%20the%20company%20thought%20about%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20challenged%20people%20every%20day%2C%20but%20I%20never%20saw%20him%20get%20mad%20or%20swear%20in%20my%20almost%20seven%20years%20there.%20He%20had%20this%20electric%20presence%2C%20a%20magnetism%20to%20him%20that%20was%20unmistakable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-worst-parts-about-working-at-amazon-according-to-employees-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20could%20be%20a%20horrible%20place%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20still%20a%20customer%20and%20don't%20boycott%20them%20because%20of%20their%20practices%2C%20though%20I%20disagree%20with%20some%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20worked%20at%20Amazon%2C%20there%20was%20this%20pressure%20that%20everybody%20had%20to%20work%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20people%20avoided%20asking%20for%20time%20off.%20Some%20employees%20would%20berate%20others.%20A%20friend%20of%20mine%20worked%20in%20a%20closet%20because%20that's%20the%20only%20place%20where%20there%20was%20room%20for%20a%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20what%20I%20could%20tell%2C%20Jeff%20is%20a%20hear-no-evil%2C%20see-no-evil%20kind%20of%20person%20who%20was%20focused%20on%20the%20mission.%20It%20didn't%20matter%20if%20the%20toilet%20was%20dirty%20or%20if%20engineers%20were%20being%20paged%20all%20night%20long.%20He%20seemed%20to%20only%20care%20if%20it%20started%20slowing%20him%20down.%20Maybe%20that's%20the%20kind%20of%20leader%20you%20have%20to%20be.%20Successful%20leaders%20don't%20take%20no%20for%20an%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-working-with-billionaires-elon-musk-jeff-bezos-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorking%20with%20Jeff%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20his%20leadership%20team%20was%20normally%20calm%20and%20serious%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20urgency%2C%20like%20in%20a%20war%20room.%20People%20were%20very%20cautious%20with%20their%20words%20around%20him.%20When%20people%20raised%20concerns%20to%20him%2C%20he'd%20sometimes%20laugh%20in%20their%20faces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20Amazon%20employees%20could%20never%20say%20if%20something%20bad%20was%20happening%20at%20Amazon.%20You%20could%20be%20brave%20and%20raise%20issues%2C%20but%20you%20were%20swimming%20against%20the%20stream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20years%20after%20I%20left%20Amazon%2C%20I%20accidentally%20publicly%20shared%20a%20private%20post%20about%20working%20at%20Google%20and%20Amazon%20where%20I%20described%20Jeff%20as%20a%20control%20freak.%20The%20post%20blew%20up%20and%20made%20it%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FBL-DGB-23338%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20heard%20through%20the%20grapevine%20Jeff%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20post%20and%20got%20a%20laugh%20out%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20was%20likable%2C%20so%20I%20was%20glad%20to%20hear%20he%20wasn't%20angry.%20He%20consistently%20came%20across%20as%20calm%20and%20keenly%20interested%20in%20everything%20everyone%20has%20to%20say.%20He%20wasn't%20afraid%20to%20ask%20questions%20or%20appear%20ignorant.%20He%20was%20never%20difficult%20to%20work%20with%2C%20even%20though%20he%20could%20be%20difficult%20to%20work%20%3Cem%3Efor%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20times%20because%20of%20his%20super-high%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20tries%20to%20keep%20things%20very%20real%2C%20and%20it's%20kind%20of%2