kids%20we'd%20passed%20along%20clothes%20to%2C%20wondering%20if%20they%20still%20had%20them%20to%20return%20now%20that%20theirs%20had%20outgrown%20them.%20I%20scoured%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-facebook-groups-market-small-businesses-build-communities-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elocal%20community%20groups%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20hoping%20to%20find%20all%20the%20baby%20items%20I%20had%20once%20eagerly%20sold%20or%20donated%2C%20assuming%20my%20family%20was%20complete.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20most%20of%20all%2C%20I%20worried.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20older%20two%20were%20finally%20at%20an%20age%20where%20sleep%20wasn't%20a%20constant%20stressor.%20I'd%20rediscovered%20my%20hobbies%2C%20got%20back%20into%20the%20swing%20of%20my%20fitness%20routine%2C%20and%20started%20writing%20again.%20I%20was%20reconnecting%20with%20myself%20as%20they%20gained%20more%20independence.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20logistics%20of%20our%20life%20had%20become%20simpler.%20I%20could%20plan%20trips%20without%20concern%20for%20accidents%20if%20we%20didn't%20stop%20at%20enough%20public%20restrooms%2C%20or%20unexpected%20naps%20that%20would%20ruin%20bedtime%20later.%20And%20now%2C%20here%20I%20was%2C%20back%20at%20the%20beginning.%20Then%2C%20a%20bigger%20worry%20set%20in%3A%20What%20would%20this%20new%20sibling%20mean%20for%20my%20older%20kids%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20bond%20was%20close%3A%20sometimes%20beautiful%2C%20sometimes%20complicated%2C%20as%20much%20about%20rivalry%20as%20it%20was%20about%20love.%20I%20wondered%20how%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-third-child-kid-can-change-family-unexpected-ways-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eyounger%20sibling%20would%20change%20that%20dynamic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20how%20I%20would%20balance%20my%20attention%20between%20a%20newborn%20and%20two%20increasingly%20independent%20elementary-aged%20kids.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22359cbb5c-295d-4edc-8005-6120c76f6113%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20a%20newborn%20again%20was%20tough%20sometimes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20few%20months%20were%20a%20blur.%20I%20had%20forgotten%20how%20demanding%20newborns%20could%20be.%20It%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20relearn%20how%20to%20care%20for%20a%20baby.%20After%20all%2C%20I%20hadn't%20held%20a%20newborn%20since%20my%20middle%20child%20was%20one.%20And%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20if%20I'd%20remember%20how%20to%20do%20any%20of%20it%2C%20let%20alone%20juggle%20it%20all%20while%20being%20the%20mom%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20to%20a%206-%20and%208-year-old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20early%20days%20were%20fraught.%20It%20was%20summer%2C%20and%20I%20longed%20to%20take%20them%20to%20the%20lake%2C%20to%20the%20water%20park%2C%20to%20do%20all%20the%20fun%20summer%20things%20we'd%20always%20enjoyed.%20Instead%2C%20I%20was%20stuck%20in%20bed%2C%20nursing%20on%20demand%2C%20mourning%20the%20time%20I%20was%20missing%20with%20them.%20There%20were%20tears%20%E2%80%94%20lots%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20from%20all%20of%20us%2C%20as%20we%20adjusted%20to%20the%20new%20rhythm%20of%20our%20family.%20They%20were%20old%20enough%20to%20understand%20why%20the%20new%20baby%20needed%20so%20much%20of%20my%20time%20and%20attention%2C%20but%20jealousy%20and%20sadness%20still%20crept%20in.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ec0ff72-bd60-4faa-ae5e-63b5a9112220%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20time%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20had%20nothing%20to%20worry%20about%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELittle%20by%20little%2C%20though%2C%20as%20my%20youngest%20reached%20new%20milestones%2C%20it%20got%20easier.%20On%20the%20first%20day%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprepare-kids-back-to-school-season-tips-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eback%20to%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20fall%2C%20my%20older%20two%20argued%20over%20who%20would%20get%20to%20push%20the%20stroller%20on%20the%20walk.%20What%20I%20had%20feared%20would%20be%20resentment%20transformed%20into%20affection%2C%20pride%2C%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20responsibility.%20The%20joy%20of%20watching%20her%20grow%20old%20enough%20to%20engage%20with%20them%20was%20immeasurable.%20That%20first%20belly%20laugh%20from%20her%20%E2%80%94%20directed%20at%20one%20of%20their%20silly%20faces%20%E2%80%94%20became%20one%20of%20my%20most%20cherished%20memories.%20At%20that%20moment%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20would%20all%20be%20OK.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20time%2C%20something%20surprising%20began%20to%20happen.%20My%20older%20kids%20adapted%20to%20their%20new%20roles%20with%20incredible%20ease.%20The%20biggest%20milestone%20came%20when%20they%20started%20teaching%20her%20things.%20It%20started%20small%20%E2%80%94%20my%20daughter%20teaching%20her%20how%20to%20stack%20blocks%2C%20my%20son%20helping%20her%20learn%20new%20words%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20could%20see%20the%20magic%20happening.%20Often%2C%20I'd%20find%20all%20three%20of%20them%20cuddled%20up%20on%20the%20couch%2C%20the%20older%20two%20explaining%20the%20best%20parts%20of%20a%20beloved%20TV%20show%20and%20explaining%20the%20characters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bond%20between%20them%20deepened%20as%20my%20youngest%20began%20interacting%20more%20with%20her%20siblings.%20She%20learned%20to%20walk%20and%20followed%20them%20everywhere.%20Now%2C%20when%20she's%20upset%2C%20sometimes%20she%20runs%20to%20one%20of%20them%20instead%20of%20me.%20Of%20course%2C%20I'm%20careful%20not%20to%20let%20them%20do%20too%20much.%20I%20balance%20their%20desire%20to%20help%20and%20mentor%20with%20making%20sure%20they%20don't%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F